        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 7:04PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 704 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Melvern, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to outdoor objects and vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Quenemo, Williamsburg, Melvern, and Pomona.

This includes Interstate 35 between mile markers 162 and 175.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
